    "abstract": "<jats:title>Abstract</jats:title>\n                <jats:p>\n                  <jats:italic>In vitro</jats:italic>\n                  selection of remdesivir-resistant SARS-CoV-2 revealed the emergence of a V166L substitution, located outside of the polymerase active site of the nsp12 protein, after 9 passages. V166L remained the only nsp12 substitution after 17 passages at a final concentration of 10 \u00b5M RDV, conferring a 2.3-fold increase in EC\n                  <jats:sub>50</jats:sub>\n                  . When V166L was introduced into a recombinant SARS-CoV-2 virus, a 1.5-fold increase in EC\n                  <jats:sub>50</jats:sub>\n                  was observed, indicating a high\n                  <jats:italic>in vitro</jats:italic>\n                  barrier to RDV resistance.\n                </jats:p>",
